Known platforms: Linux, MSWin

Play a short sample rapidly over one or more updates - SoundSource or SoundSource3D.

e.g., code like this executed in rapid succession (on same or different updates):

``` C++
String soundResourceName("Sounds/UI/switch_on.wav");
Node* soundNode(scene->CreateChild(soundResourceName));
SoundSource* soundSource(soundNode->CreateComponent<SoundSource>());
soundSource->SetSoundType(SOUND_MASTER);
soundSource->SetGain(1.0f);
soundSource->Play(GetSubsystem<ResourceCache>()->GetResource<Sound>(soundResourceName));
soundSource->SetAutoRemove(true);
```
- Does not occur between different sound resources.
- Occurs with a variety of file and sample formats.
- Issue was noticed at least as far back as 1.4

One suggestion was a possible mutex lock..

